  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">STI capacity building and policy development in Pacific SIDS</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Pacific SIDS are only beginning to realise the added-value of nurturing and developing the ST&amp;I sector and institutional and human capacity has much potential to grow. Based on a Ministerial communiqu&#xE9; in which Pacific SIDS requested UNESCO&apos;s support, the priority is to mobilize extrabudgetary funds, which requires an increased profile for UNESCO&apos;s expertise in STI in the Pacific. Therefore, the initial focus will be on supporting Pacific SIDS to develop and/or implement their ST&amp;I policies. Work is on-going with Samoa for the development of STI policy and with Papua New Guinea for use of Go-SPIN and SAGA tools to evaluate and improve the country&apos;s ST&amp;I policy. Support will be extended to Fiji and other Pacific SIDS as resources permit.</narrative>
  </description>
